entries.meaning: (Australia) An Australian freshwater crayfish of the genus Cherax, especially Cherax destructor.
examples: Having arrived at night I can speak with some authority on the desolate feeling the road produces: the white fire-scarred trunks, the unsettling vision of yabbies moving from one side of the road to the other.

entries.meaning: (Australia) A species of marine ghost shrimp, Trypaea australiensis, widely harvested by recreational anglers as bait.

verbs.description: yabby (third-person singular simple present yabbies, present participle yabbying, simple past and past participle yabbied)

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To search, forage, or fish for yabbies.
